 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Competitive Intelligence Analyst RapidAI San Mateo, CA 94402 Full-time Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description About RapidAI 
Rapid is an AI-powered healthcare platform that is changing the way patients with life-threatening conditions get care. Our technology platform offers clinical decision support, team communication & workflow tools, and analytics to create the care pathways in the network all the way from the home to the hospital so patients get to the right place at the right time for the right care. Our platform supports stroke and pulmonary embolism today with a near-term focus on expanding to other acute diseases. 
About this role 
RapidAI is in and every-changing space with ambitious goals and are looking for a Competitive Intelligence Analyst to help drive our go to market efforts by understanding the competitive and broader market landscape 
We are seeking a passionate professional who understands healthcare AI technology and can partner with product and strategy team to inform our strategy and positioning. 
This role will report to the VP of Product Management & Strategy. 
 Role Responsibilities 
Partnering with the VP of Product and Management team to conduct comprehensive research on and analysis of companies, industries, markets, competitors and deliver objective, meaningful insights in concise, compelling ways 
Work with product and marketing to develop compelling positioning, messaging and launch processes that differentiate our platform and products 
Prepare content such as battle cards, playbooks and presentations, and maintain assets (keeping them current and actionable). Train sales and go-to-market teams on an on-going basis. 
Drive creation of compelling and articulate competitive content geared towards a variety of key internal stakeholders, including executive management. 
Support deals with differentiated competitive positioning and market intelligence 
Market scan and execute competitive win/loss reviews with sales/account teams, prospects and customers to ensure clear understanding of competitive dynamics 
Collaborate with product teams to influence product roadmap and contribute to product strategy as an informed product/market expert 
Develop a regular cadence of company-wide briefings and department specific updates (Company all hands, Product Summits, C-staff meetings, Sales Kickoff, Sales & Success Training) 
 Basic Qualifications/ “Must-Haves” 
3-5 years experience in a role that emphasizes research and qualitative and quantitative analysis, including (but not limited to): product marketing, market research, healthcare management consulting, competitive intelligence, investment banking or or product management 
Experience in healthcare AI or saas 
Excellent research, analysis skills, and project management skills 
Logical and critical thinker; able to identify and apply relevant qualitative and quantitative data.. And to structure and present both qualitative and quantifiable data in a compelling fashion. 
Comfortable in a fast-paced environment, manage multiple projects simultaneously 
Proven technical knowledge and aptitude. 
Exceptional communication skills (oral and written) with a knack for decomposing problems and communicating across multiple disciplines and succinctly articulating technical concepts. 
Strong passion for software and other disruptive technologies 
Outcomes-driven: Focused on constantly moving the team forward towards the objective. Able to anticipate and remove obstacles to make the team successful 
Entrepreneurial drive and attitude, strong desire for ownership 
Ability to navigate ambiguity and demonstrate an informed point of view 
Bachelor’s Degree in Marketing, Engineering, Science, Business Administration or other related field 
 Desired Characteristics/ “Nice-to-Haves” 
MBA or equivalent higher degree (Master) 
Health-tech experience 
Startup experience 
Software experience 
BONUS: Experience building software for physicians 
 We are installed in over 1,800 hospitals in the world, have over 16,000 healthcare providers on our apps, are cleared in 60+ markets, and proven to speed up time to patient treatment, resulting in better patient outcomes. We process roughly ⅓ of all stroke patients in the US, a large number of stroke cases in other countries of the world, including Switzerland, Japan, Australia and Brazil. We’ve processed more than 2 million scans and are growing rapidly. 
 
